news.title: Rajasthan government waives 'lease money' of flats sold to MLAs
news.para: These flats were already sold to the MLAs at half the cost during the Covid-19 time. Now the urban development and housing (UDH) minister has waived the lease money. The move will cause a Rs 4 crore loss to the state exchequer, said sources.

news.title: Put on notice those behind illegal constructions: Bombay HC
news.para: Taking a tough stand against unauthorised constructions, the Bombay high court on Monday said those responsible for them must “be put on notice”. It gave the direction while hearing a PIL that alleged a floor space index (FSI) scam in Navi Mumbai.

news.title: Lucknow development body lowers interest rates to attract home buyers
news.para: Earlier, the LDA used to charge 9, 10, 11 and 13% interest rate respectively for EWS, LIG, MIG/HIG residential properties, and commercial properties, but from now on existing customers and future property buyers would be charged 7, 8, 9 and 11% respectively for the properties.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government kicks off vigilance probe into Hi-Tech township policy
news.para: In 2005, the then government had come up with the Hi-Tech policy and assigned two developers - Wave Group and Sun City - to build a township on 8,700 acres off NH-9.

news.title: Rs 10.7 crore collected in stamp duty in one day, 'highest ever' in Ghaziabad
news.para: This is the highest single-day revenue collection from stamp duty and registration charges since 2016 and also the highest so far this year, according to officials.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC's property tax inflow for six months just 10% of year's target
news.para: However, the property tax collection for the same period in the last financial year was Rs 603 crore. According to officials, collection in the tax mostly picks up towards the end of the financial year, so there is no reason for concern yet.

news.title: Larsen & Toubro subsidiary inks pact to transfer 15 acres of land to Brookfield
news.para: The land parcel will be transferred through a nearly 50-year lease for a total deal value of around Rs 1,020 crore.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires seven acres land parcel in Bengaluru
news.para: The project is estimated to have a developable potential of approximately 0.6 million sq ft of saleable area and will have an estimated booking value potential of approximately Rs 750 crore, the company said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: New York Life Insurance to invest Rs 196 crore in a commercial project of Max Estates in Noida
news.para: The land spread across 4 acre in Sector 129, Noida was acquired by Max Estates, the real estate arm of Max group, from Axis Bank for Rs 220 crore in August.

news.title: Bombay HC appoints court receiver for OJAS Tradelease's Ahmedabad mall
news.para: The court has also restrained the Future Group company OJAS Tradelease and Mall Management from creating any third-party rights or lien on the property until the final ruling.

news.title: Delhi HC quashes ED's ECIR against Indiabulls Housing and its employees
news.para: ​The high court, in an order passed on Monday, also set aside the Look Out Circulars (LOC) issued against those employees and said there shall be no search, seizure or summons arising out of the Enforcement Case Information Report (ECIR).

news.title: Birla Corporation commits $1 billion to ramp up capacity to 30 MT in eight years
news.para: ​The plan entails the installation of a four-million tonne per annum each capacity in a greenfield project and brownfield expansion. While a two million tonne output increase will come from the de-bottlenecking of existing facilities.

news.title: SBI moves NCLT to initiate insolvency against Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: Jaiprakash Associates' lease for some of the land under the jurisdiction of Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority has also been cancelled as the company failed to pay the dues.

news.title: Germany's Vonovia maintains right to evict tenants even as energy bills explode
news.para: In a step-by-step model, the company would reach out individually to the tenant to look for a solution for late payment, including informing them about how to obtain state aid, with an eviction notice seen as a last resort.

news.title: Government-owned firm steps in to complete four China Evergrande projects
news.para: Evergrande has introduced Shenzhen Longgang Ancheng Investment Operation Co Ltd into four developments situated in the Longgang district.
